      <section eId="sec_37_1009">
        <num>37-1009</num>
        <heading>Reporting</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>assembles or substantially assembles electronic displays\nfor sale in the state;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>manufactures electronic displays, under its\nown brand name or under any other brand name, for sale in the state;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nsells, under its own brand name, electronic displays in the state;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nowns a brand name that it licenses to another person for use on\nelectronic displays sold in the state;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>imports electronic displays\nfor sale in the state; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_1009__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>manufactures electronic displays for sale\nin the state without affixing a brand name.\n  2. Beginning one year after the effective date of this title, no\nelectronic display shall be sold in the state unless the manufacturer\nhas submitted an annual report identifying all of the organohalogen\nflame retardant chemicals used in the enclosure or stand of the\nelectronic display in a form determined by the department.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
